events.description: The release of manufacturing production data for the Philippines for the month of December 2025.

facts.fact_text: Manufacturing production in the Philippines grew by 1.9% year-on-year in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: Manufacturing production in the Philippines climbed 1.9% year-on-year in December 2025

facts.fact_text: The manufacturing production figure for November was revised downward to a 1% decline.

evidences.evidence_text: recovering from a downwardly revised 1% decline in the previous month

facts.fact_text: The manufacture of non-metallic mineral products increased by 29.5% in December.

evidences.evidence_text: manufacture of other non-metallic mineral products (29.5% vs 4.4% in November)

facts.fact_text: Seasonally adjusted monthly industrial activity increased by 4.7% in December.

evidences.evidence_text: On a seasonally adjusted monthly basis, industrial activity jumped 4.7%

claims.claim_text: The recovery in manufacturing production was primarily driven by the non-metallic mineral products sector.

evidences.evidence_text: mainly driven by a faster annual increase in the manufacture of other non-metallic mineral products (29.5% vs 4.4% in November), which contributed 23.2% to the overall uptrend in manufacturing production

evidence.evidence_text: mainly driven by a faster annual increase in the manufacture of other non-metallic mineral products (29.5% vs 4.4% in November), which contributed 23.2% to the overall uptrend
Activity also rebounded in machinery and equipment except electrical (9.7% vs -11.1%)
Philippine Industrial Output Recovers to 4-Month High
